# Requirements — DynamoDB `{{tableName}}` ({{businessDomain}}/{{serviceDomain}})

## Identification

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Business domain | `{{businessDomain}}` |
| Service domain | `{{serviceDomain}}` |
| Table short name | `{{tableName}}` |
| Project version | `{{versionProject}}` |
| Owner / squad | `{{owner}}` |
| Journey | `{{journey}}` |
| Feature | `{{feature}}` |

**Provisioned table name** (per env):
```
dyn-{env}-io-{{businessDomain}}-{{serviceDomain}}-{{tableName}}-{{versionProject}}
```

## Functional requirements

- **FR-1 (Key schema)**: Partition key `{{hashKeyName}}` ({{hashKeyType}}){{#if hasRangeKey}}, sort key `{{rangeKeyName}}` ({{rangeKeyType}}){{else}} — no sort key (single-item-per-partition access pattern){{/if}}.
{{#if ttlEnabled}}
- **FR-2 (TTL)**: Items carry attribute `{{ttlAttributeName}}` (Number, epoch seconds). DynamoDB deletes expired items automatically within 48 h. Attribute is optional per item — absence means no expiry.
{{/if}}
{{#if streamEnabled}}
- **FR-3 (Streams)**: DynamoDB Streams enabled with view type `{{streamViewType}}`. Consumers subscribe via stream ARN published to Parameter Store. At-least-once delivery; consumers must be idempotent.
{{/if}}
{{#if enableKinesisDestination}}
- **FR-4 (Kinesis destination)**: Table replicates change records to a Kinesis Data Stream for analytics / fan-out. Kinesis stream ARN provided by the data platform team. Precision: `MICROSECOND`.
{{/if}}
{{#if enableResourcePolicy}}
- **FR-5 (Cross-account access)**: PCI account `{{pciAccountId}}` must have `dynamodb:GetItem`, `dynamodb:PutItem`, `dynamodb:Query` on this table via resource policy (no VPC or IAM role assumption required).
{{/if}}
{{#if (gt gsiCount "0")}}
- **FR-6 (GSIs)**: {{gsiCount}} Global Secondary Index(es) to support secondary access patterns (see Design). Each GSI must have documented access pattern before provisioning.
{{/if}}
{{#if (gt lsiCount "0")}}
- **FR-7 (LSIs)**: {{lsiCount}} Local Secondary Index(es) on the base partition key. LSIs are immutable after creation — schema must be finalized before first deploy.
{{/if}}

## Non-functional requirements

- **NFR-1 (Durability)**: Point-in-Time Recovery (PITR) enabled — hardcoded by module. 35-day restore window. Deletion protection `{{deletionProtectionEnabled}}`.
- **NFR-2 (Capacity)**: Billing mode `{{billingMode}}`.{{#eq billingMode "PROVISIONED"}} Auto-scaling with 70% utilization target on read and write capacity. Define initial capacity per GSI and base table.{{/eq}}
- **NFR-3 (Encryption)**: Server-side encryption with customer-managed KMS key (`data.aws_kms_key.dynamodb.arn` from shared security account). Key rotation enabled.
- **NFR-4 (Table class)**: `{{tableClass}}`.{{#eq tableClass "STANDARD_INFREQUENT_ACCESS"}} Access pattern is infrequent; IA class reduces storage cost but increases per-request cost. Validate access frequency assumption.{{/eq}}
- **NFR-5 (Observability)**: CloudWatch alarms on `UserErrors`, `SystemErrors`, `ThrottledRequests` ≥ 1. Metrics forwarded to central monitoring account.
- **NFR-6 (Access control)**: Least-privilege IAM. Consumer Lambdas/services granted only the actions they use (`GetItem`, `PutItem`, `UpdateItem`, `Query`, etc.) scoped to table ARN and specific GSI ARNs.

## Constraints

- Module source: `app.terraform.io/IO-BANKING/cloud-dynamodb/module`. Pin to latest certified version.
- No `dynamodb:Scan` granted to service roles. Operator tooling access only via separate role with audit trail.
- Item size target ≤ 4 KB. Larger attributes off-loaded to S3; table stores reference key only.
- LSI schema is immutable. GSI schema (key attributes) is immutable after creation.
- Cross-account access only via resource policy — no sts:AssumeRole from PCI account to iomvp accounts.

## Acceptance criteria

- [ ] Table deploys to all target environments without error.
- [ ] Provisioned table name matches convention `dyn-{env}-io-{{businessDomain}}-{{serviceDomain}}-{{tableName}}-{{versionProject}}`.
- [ ] KMS encryption active (SSE shows CMK ARN in `describe-table` output).
- [ ] PITR enabled (`describe-continuous-backups` returns `PointInTimeRecoveryStatus: ENABLED`).
- [ ] Deletion protection `{{deletionProtectionEnabled}}`.
{{#if ttlEnabled}}
- [ ] TTL enabled on attribute `{{ttlAttributeName}}` (`describe-time-to-live` returns `TimeToLiveStatus: ENABLED`).
{{/if}}
{{#if streamEnabled}}
- [ ] Stream ARN published to SSM `/io/{env}/{{businessDomain}}/{{serviceDomain}}/{{tableName}}/stream-arn`.
- [ ] Stream view type = `{{streamViewType}}`.
{{/if}}
{{#if (gt gsiCount "0")}}
- [ ] All {{gsiCount}} GSI(s) active and matching agreed key schema.
{{/if}}
{{#if enableResourcePolicy}}
- [ ] Resource policy grants PCI account `{{pciAccountId}}` only `GetItem`, `PutItem`, `Query`. Verified with `get-resource-policy` CLI.
{{/if}}
- [ ] Table ARN and name published to SSM (`/io/{env}/{{businessDomain}}/{{serviceDomain}}/{{tableName}}/{table-arn,table-name}`).
- [ ] Tags present: `BUSINESS-DOMAIN`, `SERVICE-DOMAIN`, `JOURNEY`, `FEATURE`, `REPOSITORY`, `OWNER`.
- [ ] No CDK Nag / tfsec violations in CI (Terraform plan succeeds clean).

